        "International career": "Opoku was a part of the Ghana under 17 squad that competed in 2013 African U-17 Championship. He has also represented the Ghana under-20 team.In July 2017, Opoku made his senior international debut in a 2–1 defeat against United States. He came as a 38th minute substitute for Rashid Sumaila following his knee injury.In April 2021, The Court of Arbitration for Sport asked Tunisian side Club Africain to pay him US$279,500 after  repeated failure to be pay his salary, which lead  termination of  his contract wihh the club  in June 2018."
